Description: Rim (not quite preserved) sherd of North Ionian black-figured pottery bowl; interior: key maeander between bands at rim; lotus bud and flower frieze below; exterior: stopt maeander betwwen bands at rim; black-figure frieze below; swan to right; perhaps tail of bird at right break; blobs as fill.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.227)
